						<summary>

						<p>Left door-jamb (middle portion) of the Mūlēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1183,</hi> expressed in chronogram <hi rend="italic">Guṇō-bha-Tri-ṇayana.,</hi> corresponding to 1261 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Seems to register gift of a lamp by Nārana, son of Rāyanāmātya. Also mentions Pōturaju, Dēvarāju and Śivadēva. The gift is made probably to god sakalēśvaradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
